# When present, this file REPLACES .gitignore for EAS build archives.
# It exists so that `eas build --local` (and any other EAS build flow that
# bundles the project tree) can ship three gitignored files that the build
# needs but that we do not want in version control:
#
#   - .env.local                   (used by Metro/Expo to load SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN
#                                   so Sentry source maps upload during builds)
#   - google-services.json         (Firebase Android config required by prebuild)
#   - GoogleService-Info.plist     (Firebase iOS config required by prebuild)
#
# Background: EAS local builds tarball the project respecting .gitignore;
# secret-visibility EAS env vars are NOT injected into local builds. Combined,
# those two facts mean the only way local builds see these files is to let them
# ride along in the archive — which is exactly what this file enables.
#
# IMPORTANT: keep this file in sync with .gitignore. If you add a new exclusion
# to .gitignore, mirror it here too — otherwise the file will leak into EAS
# build archives.

# dependencies
node_modules/

# Expo
.expo/
dist/
web-build/
expo-env.d.ts

# Native
.kotlin/
*.orig.*
*.jks
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision

# Metro
.metro-health-check*

# debug
npm-debug.*
yarn-debug.*
yarn-error.*

# macOS
.DS_Store
*.pem

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo

app-example

# Native folders
/android/
/ios/

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.code-workspace

# Firebase
firebase-debug.log
# NOTE: /GoogleService-Info.plist and /google-services.json intentionally NOT
# excluded here — they need to ship to EAS builds. They remain gitignored.

# Claude
.claude/
# NOTE: .env.local intentionally NOT excluded here — see header comment.

# Misc
.superpowers/

# Git worktrees
.worktrees/

# Fastlane
fastlane/.private/
fastlane/.tmp/
fastlane/report.xml
fastlane/README.md
fastlane/ios/metadata/review_information/*
!fastlane/ios/metadata/review_information/notes.txt
.env.fastlane.local
